f \"place of [the] main body of an army\" for {{lang|mi|\u014chope}}.<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://nzhistory.govt.nz/culture/maori-language-week/1000-maori-place-names |title=1000 M\u0101ori place names|publisher=New Zealand Ministry for Culture and Heritage|date=6 August 2019}}</ref> On 10 October 1974, the name of the settlement was formally changed from Ohope Beach to Ohope.<ref><!-- this is the entry for Ohope Beach -->{{cite web |title=New Zealand Gazetteer |url= https://gazetteer.linz.govt.nz/place/50496 |publisher=[[New Zealand Geographic Board]] |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> \nOn 21 June 2019, the official name of the town was subsequently changed to \u014chope (with a [[Macron (diacritic)|macron]]) by the [[New Zealand Geographic Board]].\n<ref><!-- this is the entry for \u014chope -->{{cite web |title=NZGB Notices \u2014 June 2019 |url= https://www.linz.govt.nz/regulatory/place-names/recent-place-name-notices-and-place-names-interest/nzgb-notices-%E2%80%93-june-2019]] |accessdate=25 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Holiday destination==\nIt is a popular holiday destination during the New Zealand summer, with several kilometres of safe [[human swimming|swimming]] beaches. The western end of the beach is popular for [[surfing]] during the summer and Christmas period.\n\n==Town facilities==\n\u014chope is also home to the [[Ohope Beach Primary School]], which has five classrooms.\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nimage:Ohope Tua Tuas.JPG|Digging for [[tuatua]] on \u014chope Beach in summer\nimage:Ohope overview.JPG| \u014chope from above\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Ohope Beach}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.whakatane.govt.nz/services/parks-and-public-spaces/coastal-reserves-and-beaches Coastal Reserves and Beaches, Whakatane District Council]\n\n{{coord|-37.9648|177.0434|region:NZ_type:landmark|display=title}}\n[[Category:Whakatane District]]\n[[Category:Beaches of the Bay of Plenty Region]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in th